This paper is about knowledge graph embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed model involves deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (cs.LG) and graph convolutional networks (cs.CL). The model is applied to knowledge base completion, which is a task related to databases (cs.DB). Finally, the model is trained using optimization techniques such as backpropagation (cs.NE).
